    <body>
      <section name="Installation">
       <span class='shortdesc'>How to install Hippo CMS</span>
        <p>
          To run Hippo CMS, a 
          <a href="in_servlet_container.html"><span class='index' id='servlet_container'>Java servlet container</span></a> 
          or a 
          <a href="in_application_server.html"><span class='index' id='application_server'>Java application server</span></a> 
          is needed.
        </p>
        <p>
          Hippo supplies a Java <span class='index' id='WAR'>WAR</span> package to deploy in Java servlet containers and
          a <span class='index' id='EAR'>EAR</span> package to deploy in Java application servers. 
        </p>
        <p>Compatible Java servlet containers:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><a href='http://tomcat.apache.org/'>Apache Tomcat</a></li>
            <li><a href='http://jetty.mortbay.com/jetty/'>Jetty</a></li> 
          </ul>
        <p>Compatible Java application servers:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><a href='https://glassfish.dev.java.net/'>Sun Glassfish</a></li>
            <li><a href='http://www.jboss.org/'>JBoss</a></li>
            <!--
            <li><a href='http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/'>IBM WebSphere Application Server</a></li>
            <li><a href='http://www.bea.com/framework.jsp?CNT=index.htm&amp;FP=/content/products/weblogic/server'>Oracle Bea WebLogic Server</a></li>
            -->
          </ul>
      </section>
